{
  "stem": "10446.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And another group of Nazi investors were also vying for it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So-- until finally, everything was written over to the Nazi party, without any compensation whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "That's when they-- my mother and Hella got the immigration visas.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was six months.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We could do absolutely nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had transit visas in France.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had no work permit.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We could just sit and wait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was a terrible time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Calling my mother and my wife was dangerous, because the wires were tapped.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we corresponded.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we-- through somebody who came out, we arranged a secret code.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The fifth letter of every letter-- of every line in the letter would make a sentence-- you know, written-- read vertically.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So it took hours and hours to compose one letter, if you wanted to convey any message.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's how we communicated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and finally, we could not do anything at all, except wait.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a very difficult time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had some money outside of the country, which happened to be money that we had sent to our representative for business purposes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's what we lived on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I also had smuggled some money to England-- not very much, but just enough to see us through.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One time-- and it was in 1936-- I still had my passport.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we still had-- we had business connections with England, selling hops.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My father had some money put aside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And unbeknownst to him, I took it out of the safe and put it in my pocket, and took it with me on that trip.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And again, I took a sleeping car to be safe, on the way to Belgium, and then from Belgium by ship to England.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
